news.title: Whiteland Corporation invests ₹5,600 crore in Westin Residences Gurugram
news.para: The project will span across 7.78 hectares (approximately 20 acres), with 1,700 three-bedroom and four-bedroom residences ranging from 248 to 402 sq meters (approximately 2,673 to 4,328 sq ft).

news.title: Adani Realty, Emaar Group said to cease talks on Indian real estate unit sale
news.para: The Adani family and Emaar had been in talks for a sale of Emaar India Ltd. at an enterprise value of $1.4 billion, Bloomberg News reported in March. Two months prior, Emaar said it was in discussions with potential buyers in India, including Adani.

news.title: Embassy Developments posts ₹123.04 crore profit in Q4 FY25
news.para: Embassy Developments' net consolidated total income stood at ₹1,182.61 crore in Q4 FY25 as against ₹401.54 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Asian Granito India posts ₹16.41 crore profit in Q4 FY25
news.para: Asian Granito India's net consolidated total income stood at ₹478.49 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 11.78 per cent from ₹428.06 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shapoorji Pallonji Group secures $3.4 billion in private credit deal
news.para: About a dozen large investors - some using multiple funds - bought zero-coupon rupee bonds that offer a yield of 19.75%, the people said, asking not to be identified because the information is private. The debt matures in three years.

news.title: Residents of BDD chawls in Worli will get homes before July: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Shelar, a senior BJP MLA and guardian minister of Mumbai's suburban district, made the announcement while inspecting the progress of the redevelopment towers being constructed under the first phase of the Worli BDD Chawl Redevelopment Project.

news.title: Maharashtra CM approves Dharavi master plan
news.para: A press release stated that CM Devendra Fadnavis directed the Dharavi redevelopment to be done in an environmentally friendly manner, integrating its commercial sector. He said priority should be given to the rehabilitation of skilled artisans.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's profit up 4.7% to ₹50.45 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: The company had reported a net profit of Rs 48.16 crore in the January-March quarter a year ago, HeidelbergCement India said in a regulatory filing on Wednesday.

news.title: Ektanagari relocation to cost ₹1,500 crore, buildings within floodline will be razed: MoS
news.para: ​The proposal involves relocation of as many as 1,383 homes and at least 67 shops from the flood-prone ‘blue zones' of Ektanagari, Vitthalnagar and Nimbajnagar to municipal land in Hingne Khurd survey no. 19.

news.title: EFC (I)'s net profit grows 71.72% in Q4 FY25
news.para: EFC (I)'s net consolidated total income stood at ₹216.39 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 118.33 per cent from ₹99.11 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kanakia, Hines, Mitsubishi Estate & Sumitomo Corporation's JV to develop office space in Mumbai
news.para: The office space spread across three-acre land parcel and will offer 1.5 million sq ft. The project is being designed by Kohn Pedersen Fox (KPF).

news.title: Karnataka: Rules to tax unauthorised properties in rural areas soon
news.para: The move is part of measures to implement The Karnataka Gram Swaraj and Panchayat Raj (Amendment) Bill, 2025, which was passed in March.

news.title: Mussoorie Dehradun development body to identify land bank for residential projects
news.para: This move was prompted by the rising population density and the success of previous initiatives such as the ISBT and Aamwala Tarla residential schemes.

news.title: Ranchi civic body issues notices to PMAY beneficiaries over dues
news.para: The LHP consists of 1,008 flats spread over 5.33 acres at Aani in Dhurwa. Each flat cost around Rs 13 lakh, of which Rs 6.5 lakh was subsidised by the Union and the state govts. The rest was to be given by the beneficiaries in five instalments.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Residents file complaint against builder for occupying common areas in project
news.para: According to the complaint filed with the executive magistrate, the developer allegedly entered the premises on May 23 and demolished a boundary wall and gate in the common area.

news.title: Illegal commercial structures demolished in Kharar, Zirakpur
news.para: In Kharar, a commercial building in Gillco Valley, Sector 115, was razed after it was found to be constructed without an approved layout plan from the executive officer's office and lacking mandatory Rera registration.

news.title: NGT asks environment ministry to frame guidelines for plywood industry
news.para: The green body was hearing a matter regarding several plywood units causing pollution in a village in Yamuna Nagar district of Haryana.

news.title: No change in property tax rates, higher bills automatically due to RR rate revision: BMC
news.para: "The current revision comes after a 10-year gap. There is a legal provision that these payments will be automatically revised due to the changes made in the ready reckoner for the financial year 2025-26," the release stated.

news.title: NBCC India's net profit rises 29.10% in Q4 FY25
news.para: NBCC India has incorporated a wholly-owned subsidiary named NBCC Overseas Real Estate LLC in Dubai Mainland, (UAE) on April 23, 2025 for carrying out real estate business.

news.title: ED says DHFL promoters used public money for extravagant hobbies, lavish purchases
news.para: The Wadhawan brothers are accused of defrauding a consortium of 17 banks led by Union Bank of India (UBI) to the tune of Rs 34,615 crore.
